<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1047" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1047">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 125.8273/68.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-26">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 26, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Silliman arrived this morning. Is not very well physically. Considers
                                important should go Washington report Department soon as possible.
                                He is without funds. Will Department authorize me draw hundred
                                dollars gold for Silliman and also telegraph any instructions
                                Department deems proper for him.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>